%h3 Another iteration

%p The outcome of the session with the Scrum Master meant we had an alternative way of displaying our iterative process as well as some tweaks to our columns.

%p INSERT IMAGE

%p Our column structure was:

%ol{:id => "another-iteation"}
  %li
    %h4 Backlog
    %p The is where our ideas live. Design hypotheses. Components to look into and explore. Things to optimise. Bugs or "That's not great is its".
    %p With the product team, we routinely rank and evaluate items here. Ensuring everything has been designed and tested before being put into the product.
    %p To illustrate something is more important, it sits higher up the board.
  %li
    %h4 Research
    %p The phase where we are actively working on a problem, but exploring the shape and size of it. Looking at current solutions and the reasons they exist, as well as other people's.
  %li
    %h4 Design
    %p Here we are exploring and then refining our ideas into testable chunks of work. From sketching paper prototypes to screens or HTML.
    %p If an item has a sticky note, it has been reviewed and an indicator of an item going through some further refinement or exploration.
  %li
    %h4 Design Review
    %p Formal review time. With another designer. The idea here being that we stage a time for each and every piece of design work.
    %p Comments and suggestions are made and then saved. A sticky dot with the reviewer's initials are added.
    %p If the item is deemed to need some further work, it can go back to the design column. If it is ready for wider review or would benefit from it, it moves forward.
  %li
    %h4 Wider Review
    %p Review with the wider team/s. This ranges from informal to formal reviews with the product team to more formal processes including the wider programme, other organisations and entities.
    %p After this stage, as with the design review column, a sticky dot is added. The name or initials of the reviewers are added.
    %p The card then can return to design or move forward.
  %li
    %h4 Document
    %p A staging area where we either create or collect our design artefacts together in one place.
    %p We also add a design hypothesis (or two) to each ticket to surface our assumptions.
  %li
    %h4 User test
    %p Time to get it in front of people and work out if it has the desired outcomes.
  %li
    %h4 Done
    %p All work finished. Idea explored, built, reviewed, tested with users.

%h3 Bottlenecks

%p We found two bottlenecks very quickly with this process. Design review and document.

%p The bottlenecks were faults of our own.

%p Taking time to formally review, rather than quick glances, slowed things down.

%p It is easy to review design work and not question enough with a colleague. To give a quick glance and a supportive remark.

%p The board highlighted that we needed to review early and often.

